Help for Caregivers: You're Not Alone

   Welcome to this new resource for caregivers in Washington State. Here
   you will find information for family and other unpaid caregivers. Paid
   caregivers may also find it useful. All are welcome.
   Information and resources listed here are not comprehensive. We will
   list new information frequently - be sure to check back often.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Get your FREE copy of AASA's Caregiver Handbook. Request your copy via
   email. Be sure to include your name, mailing address, and number of
   copies.
   You may also view and download the Caregiver's Handbook in PDF Format .

  Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

   A list of the most common questions (and answers) that address the
   concerns of caregivers, plus links to brochures, books, and other
   websites.
   Visit the FAQ page

  The Washington State Family
   Caregiver Support Program

   The Family Caregiver Support Program (FCSP) provides support services
   for family and other unpaid caregivers. Services are free or low cost.
   Generally the FCSP offers: information and help getting services;
   caregiver support groups and counseling; caregiver training and
   education; and respite care.
   Certain eligibility rules apply, and services vary by geographic area.
   Find the Family Caregiver Support Program in your area
